As of Monday, South Africa reports 9 300 new cases, bringing the total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases to 373 628. The total number of deaths is 5 173. The total number of recoveries is 194 865 which translates to a total recovery rate of 52%. The total number of tests to date is 2 505 646 with 33 899 new tests conducted since the last report.  #COVID19 statistics in SA as at 20 July. pic.twitter.com/7b9VRjr1G4 — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) July 20, 2020  As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 373 628, the total number of deaths is 5173 and the total number of recoveries is 194 865. pic.twitter.com/kXpKagHsxn — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) July 20, 2020 